        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2007-12-22T13:44:42.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>Zend_View requires output buffering in order to do much of its work, and capturing template results for later manipulation with filters would be impossible without it.</p>

<p>If you are using Smarty, you should consider writing a class implementing Zend_View_Interface if you don't want the output buffering, instead of using smarty through a zend_view view script.</p>

        </div>
    </div>
