        <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2007-12-29T18:20:36.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>You can disable output buffering in the Zend_Controller family by setting the 'disableOutputBuffering' param to a true value:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$front-&gt;setParam('disableOutputBuffering', true);
</code></pre>

<p>This setting has been present since 0.6.0.</p>

